The President said women leaders would be of much help at the Senate as proposed.The President said the 2007/08 post-election violence brought in an expanded executive and it is time this was made permanent. President Uhuru Kenyatta used his Jamhuri Day address to the nation yesterday to outline what will be the main message in the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) campaigns in the New Year.
The Head of State put up a strong case for the envisaged BBI benefits, including an expanded executive to promote inclusivity, increased devolved funds to foster development in the counties, gender equity and a Judiciary ombudsman for the promotion of justice.



