The March 9, 2018 handshake between him and ODM leader Raila Odinga, the President said, was “a temporary solution to a long-term search.”
The deputy president, in his short speech, addressed the Covid-19 pandemic that has ravaged the country for the better part of the year, calling for it to be prioritised. He used the opportunity to advance his previously stated position for a non-contested referendum.
ODM leader Raila Odinga , ANC’s Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetang’ula attended the function but did not make speeches.
